Serious arson occurs if the offender burns: 

One  or  more  buildings or  edifices,  consequent  to  one  single  act  of burning,  or  as  a  result of simultaneous burnings;

(1) Any   building   devoted   to   public   utilities,   or   of   inflammable   or   explosive materials, or of public or private ownership, devoted to the public in general;
(2) Any  mode  of  transportation  or  conveyance  for  public  use,  entertainment  or leisure;
(3) Any building to conceal or destroy evidence of a crime, or to conceal bankruptcy or to commit fraud.
